data.content:
Your code **doesn't use `Thread.Abort`**, so there's nothing to migrate on that front. However, it does use raw `Thread` which is discouraged in modern .NET. Here's the guidance:

## `Thread.Abort` in .NET 8

`Thread.Abort()` throws `PlatformNotSupportedException` in .NET 6+. If you have it elsewhere, replace it with **cooperative cancellation** via `CancellationToken`.

## Recommended rewrite using `Parallel.ForEach`

```csharp
public class SimpleWorker
{
    public void RunBatch(List<WorkItem> items, CancellationToken ct = default)
    {
        Parallel.ForEach(items, item =>
        {
            ct.ThrowIfCancellationRequested();
            Process(item);
        });
    }

    private void Process(WorkItem item)
    {
        Thread.Sleep(100); // consider Task.Delay in async version
        item.Result = ComputeResult(item.Input);
    }
}
```

## Key migration points

| .NET Framework pattern | .NET 8 replacement |
|---|---|
| `Thread.Abort()` | `CancellationTokenSource.Cancel()` |
| `ThreadAbortException` | `OperationCanceledException` |
